definition: to pull/to play (a bowed instrument)/to drag/to draw/to chat

sentences.english: The tensile strength and elongation of the reticulated foams increase with the pore diameter.
sentences.chinese: 泡孔增大，则拉伸强度和伸长率降低。

sentences.english: The right leg performs knee flexion while theleft knee undergoes knee extension.

sentences.english: No deflection if the tensioning force is increased.
sentences.chinese: 如果没有力量增加拉伸变形。

sentences.english: Thus it is the densification that produces the higher tensile strength for T700 fibers.
sentences.chinese: 所以致密化赋予了T700较高的拉伸强度。

sentences.english: Genuine Italian woven cotton elastic provides stretchability for more comfort.
sentences.chinese: 真正的意大利棉梭织弹性提供更舒适的拉伸。

sentences.english: Tilt you head, bringing your right ear to your right shoulder until you feel a stretch.

sentences.english: In comparison to other leathers, deerskin offers comparatively high tensile strength.

sentences.english: In order to export the sidebar, the main content area is temporarily stretched vertically.
sentences.chinese: 为了导出侧边栏，主体区域现在暂时的使用垂直拉伸。

sentences.english: A sprain is an injury to a ligament caused by excessive stretching.

sentences.english: Twin-needle reinforced stitching with a high tensile strength thread.
sentences.chinese: 双针具有很高的拉伸强度螺纹钢筋拼接。

sentences.english: Special attention has been paid to the isothermal tensile process and the constrained recovery process.
sentences.chinese: 特别注意了桓温拉伸过程和强迫回复过程。

sentences.english: The overall Chinese BOPET film industry is growing rapidly.
sentences.chinese: 中国双向拉伸聚酯薄膜行业发展迅速。

sentences.english: Then lengthen your tailbone and sacrum as your thighbones descend toward your hamstrings.
sentences.chinese: 然后，拉伸你的尾骨和骶骨，大腿骨沉向腿筋。

sentences.english: Dyeing time would not affect both the drawing recovery and the bending recovery of PTT filament.
sentences.chinese: 但染色时间对拉伸和弯曲回弹率基本没有景响。

sentences.english: If you slouch forward when you run, you may be pulling too hard on your calf muscles.
sentences.chinese: 如果跑的时候向前弯腰，那你的腓肠肌会拉伸过量。
